The leader of the Indigenious People of Biafra IPOB, Nnamdi Kanu, has said his security network dubbed the Eastern Security Network, ESN is not a terror organisation and does not engage in criminality.  He also denied claims that ESN is behind the various attacks in the Southern part of Nigeria. Kanu on December 13 2020 launched the ESN security outfit due to the rising insecurity in the region. There have been allegations that the ESN was behind the various attacks on police formations in the South South and South Eastern parts of the country. In a tweet posted today, May 17, Kanu said operatives of the security outfit are too disciplined to be involved in criminal activities. His tweet reads: “I’ve said it before but let me say it again that the Eastern Security Network I command is strictly organized to deal with TERRORIST herdsmen in our land. ESN is a highly disciplined group of volunteers that do not engage in any act of criminality or terror”  Source The proscribed Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) has described as shameful claims by the Imo State governor, Hope Uzodinma that it hijacked Eastern Security Network (ESN) from the Southeast governors. The group said the governor resorted to what it termed as cheap blackmail following his attempt to infiltrate and possibly… In "News" •Dave Umahi, Governor of Ebonyi State We have been following with keen interest, but with cautious optimism, the recent decision by the governors of the South East Zone, after their one-day meeting in Owerri, Imo State, to establish a joint security outfit for the region, which is to be known… In "Opinion" Following threats by Chief of Naval Staff, Vice Admiral Awwal Gambo, to go after Eastern Security Network (ESN) for allegedly attacking security agents in the South East and South South, the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB), yesterday, said it would not succumb to any threat or blackmail to disband the… In "News"